1. You have 2 options for what you can pass in to a
   state setter function (e.g. `setCount`). What are they?
   
a. New value of state (setCount(42))
b. Callback function - whatever the callback function returns === new value of state


2. When would you want to pass the first option (from answer
   above) to the state setter function?

a. whenever you need to reset the value of state

3. When would you want to pass the second option (from answer
   above) to the state setter function?

b. whenever you need to changed state based on its previous value or other variables
